  "optimization_hints": [
    "Q1: Scan+filter l_shipdate (98% selectivity) → group by two low-cardinality flags → order. Use hash aggregation, vectorize date comparison, partial aggregation across threads.",
    "Q2: Selective filters on part (p_size=15, p_type LIKE '%BRASS' ~20% selectivity) + correlated subquery. Decorate MIN subquery into hash lookup, use direct array for nation/region (only 25 nations).",
    "Q3: Date range filters on orders/lineitem + low cardinality c_mktsegment. High fanout join customer→orders→lineitem. Bloom filter on customer to reduce probe volume, push date filters early.",
    "Q4: Selective date filter (25%) + EXISTS subquery. Convert EXISTS into semi-join, build hash set of l_orderkey matching date predicate, test membership in orders scan.",
    "Q5: 6-table join with date/region filters. Join order: region(5) → nation(25) → supplier(100K) → customer(1.5M) → orders → lineitem(60M). Use direct array for region/nation.",
    "Q6: Single-table scan, very selective filters (l_discount BETWEEN + l_quantity < 24). SIMD vectorization for dual predicates, early termination, no materialization.",
    "Q7: Join supplier→nation, orders→customer→nation on shipdate range. Separate two nation joins using direct array lookup, hash join supplier+customer sides.",
    "Q8: 7-table join filtered by o_orderdate and p_type LIKE. Push LIKE filter to part scan early, use partsupp to reduce probe count, direct array for regions.",
    "Q9: Correlated join on partsupp with LIKE filter on part names. Hash table on (l_suppkey, l_partkey) to match against partsupp PK, late materialization for nation names.",
    "Q10: Date range on orders (25% selectivity) + l_returnflag='R' filter. Hash aggregation on c_custkey (~50K groups), bloom filter orders before inner join on lineitem.",
    "Q11: Aggregation on partsupp with supplier nation filter. Hash table for ps_partkey (200K groups), use zone maps on ps_supplycost*ps_availqty for HAVING pruning.",
    "Q12: Hash join orders+lineitem on shipdate range with dual CASE aggregations (low cardinality l_shipmode). SIMD CASE evaluation, vectorized hash aggregation.",
    "Q13: LEFT OUTER JOIN customer→orders with pattern filter. Partial aggregation on c_custkey first, then group by c_count. Memory budget: ~1.5M customers → ~30 distinct counts.",
    "Q14: Hash join part+lineitem, selective filters (shipdate range + LIKE). Bloom filter part on p_type BEFORE probe join, vectorize CASE computation.",
    "Q15: CTE with GROUP BY on l_suppkey (100K groups), then join to supplier. Hash aggregation, reuse CTE materialization for MAX lookup.",
    "Q16: Range filter on p_size (32% selectivity) + NOT IN subquery (supplier complaints). Build hash set of complained suppliers (~2K), hash join partsupp+part with skip check.",
    "Q17: Correlated scalar subquery (0.2 * AVG(l_quantity) per part). Pre-compute averages in hash table keyed by p_partkey, decorate into main query, vectorize division.",
    "Q18: IN (SELECT...) subquery with SUM(l_quantity) > 300 HAVING. Hash aggregation on l_orderkey (15M→few K), semi-join to customer+orders, avoid materializing large intermediate.",
    "Q19: Three OR-ed complex conditions on (p_brand, p_container, l_quantity, p_size, l_shipmode, l_shipinstruct). Vectorized OR with branch prediction, bloom filter part early.",
    "Q20: IN (SELECT ps_suppkey ...) with correlated subquery on lineitem. Build hash set of (l_partkey, l_suppkey) from filtered lineitem, semi-join to partsupp.",
    "Q21: Complex EXISTS/NOT EXISTS logic with supplier nation = 'SAUDI ARABIA' (4%). Decorrelate outer query by building hash sets of matching l_orderkey, l_suppkey tuples.",
    "Q22: Correlated NOT EXISTS on customer with phone code IN list. Hash set of o_custkey from orders, semi-join to customer, vectorize phone code extraction (SUBSTRING)."
  ],
  "summary": "TPC-H scale 10 (60M lineitem rows, 15M orders, 1.5M customers). Dominated by fact-table scans (lineitem, orders) with selective date/flag filters and large multi-table joins. Parallelization critical: 64 cores must exploit thread-level + SIMD. Key optimization levers: (1) push filters early (date/region), (2) use direct array lookups for tiny dimensions (region, nation), (3) bloom filters to reduce join probe volume, (4) hash semi-joins for IN/EXISTS subqueries, (5) vectorized aggregation with partial pre-aggregation across threads."
